  "original_title": "Egg producers agree to drop prices \u2013 Minister",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Egg producers agree to drop prices \u2013 Minister",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); Minister of Trade, Commerce, and Food Security Nalin Fernando says poultry businessmen have decided to reduce the prices of eggs in the local market.",
        "The Minister said that the price of eggs will gradually drop.",
        "He said that poultry businessmen have to bear high costs due to the rise in prices of animal feed and medicines.",
        "Minister Nalin Fernando says raids will also continue to identify those selling eggs at prices above the market rate.",
        "The All Ceylon Poultry Businessmen's Association says eggs can't be sold below their cost of production, and it is impossible to sell eggs at the imposed maximum retail price.",
        "According to the Extraordinary Gazette issued on Friday, the Maximum Retail Price of a white egg is 43 rupees, while the MRP of a brown egg is 45 rupees.",
        "Sri Lanka Govt must permit the safe return of Gotabaya & Family \u2013 HRCSL"
      ],
